	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>The Lotus Peak</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_HELP">
			<Text>The mountain is angry today, Your Eminence. It is no doubt related to the man in the atrium, who comes seeking your approval.[NEWLINE]What shall we do with him?</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>The Natural Wonder permenantly yields +1 [ICON_PEACE] Faith, [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism and [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>The man's reputation is restored, gain {4_GPChange}. His school of painting flourishes, [ICON_GREAT_ARTIST] Artists in the City generate +2 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>The City's Barracks yields +2 [ICON_PEACE] Faith, and two Samurai are recruited.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Fund the Outpost to the tune of {2_InstantYield}. A Shelter is built in the City, and it generates +5 [ICON_RESEARCH] Science.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*The man begs to be allowed to scatter his wife's ashes on the mountain's slopes*[NEWLINE]This request has touched my heart. Make it so.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*The man is a painter who has produced a series of prints of the Mountain, however the local Artist's Guild won't allow him to sell them and have driven him out of business*[NEWLINE]These are really good. Let's hang them in the Palace - that ought to sort his predicament out.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*A troop of warriors who revere the mountain wish to settle in the City*[NEWLINE]If they fight for the Empire, I see no reason not to recruit these Ronin.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_FUJI_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The mountain is the highest point the City has access to, the man - a weather scientist - wishes to build a weather station on the summit to monitor the severe conditions that the City has been known to suffer*[NEWLINE]This could mean a massive reduction to loss of life and property damage in the future! Give him the money.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
